sive commentaries on the basic questions of documentary’s distinct relationship to the reality it represents, as well as close readings of provocative documentaries from this form's earliest days to its most recent incarnations. These essays offer a definitive account of what makes documentary film such a vital part of our cultural landscape.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aDocumentary filmsxHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  aacademic.  aaesthetic.  aargument.  acinema studies.  aculture.  adocumentary films.  adocumentary.  aethics.  aevidence.  afilm content.  afilm essays.  afilm form.  afilm history.  afilm scholar.  afilm studies.  afilm writing.  aform and content.  ahistory of film.  aimpact.  aintroduction.  airony.  amaking movies.  ametaphor.  amockumentary.  anarrative.  apolitical.  areal world.  arealistic.  aresearch.  asatire.  ascholarly.  ashort essays.  asocial studies.  astorytelling.  atrue stories.  atruth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052029039640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096458740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520964587423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520964587/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY